-led approach prevents many of those products from coming into the country in the first place.     Share         Manufacturing: Leaving the EU      The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh (Ochil and South Perthshire) (SNP)       Share       6. What assessment he has made of the effect of the UK’s decision to leave the EU on the manufacturing sector.  [907118]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Minister for Climate Change and Industry (Mr Nick Hurd)       Share       The UK is the ninth largest manufacturing nation in the world. My colleagues and I will continue to engage with UK manufacturing and other sectors to understand their priorities in shaping a successful Brexit and an industrial strategy that is effective in supporting competitiveness.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Ms Ahmed-Sheikh       Share       Nissan’s special deal is, of course, good news for workers there and for that sector, but does the Minister agree that my constituents in the manufacturing sector deserve a similar deal? Will he therefore provide this House with a full list of assurances given to the company and all the details provided to those investigating the potential state aid implications of that deal, so that we can assess the implications of that work for our overall manufacturing sector?     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Mr Hurd       Share       We ran through this last week in the statements that the Secretary of State made. The senior Nissan Europe executive Colin Lawther wa